[SN]TITLE[SN]
Police officer Stephen McMillan sentenced over indecent images of children

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A police officer has received a suspended 12-week sentence after pleading guilty to four charges of making indecent images of children.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stephen McMillan, 26, admitted making and distributing the images.
The Metropolitan Police officer, of Viridian Square, Aylesbury, filmed a teenage girl performing a sex act on him and sent it to three friends.
He was sentenced at High Wycombe Magistrates' Court and placed on the Sex Offenders Register for five years.
